Final Tips for Painting High-Traffic Areas
Prep Your Walls: Clean surfaces and patch any holes or imperfections before painting for the best results.
Use High-Quality Tools: A good roller and brush will ensure even coverage and a professional finish.
Apply Two Coats: Even if using one-coat paint, a second coat can add extra protection in high-use areas.
Consider Trim & Doors: Use semi-gloss or gloss paint on trim and doors for easy cleaning and added durability.
Conclusion
Choosing the best paint for high-traffic areas like hallways and kitchens ensures your walls stay fresh and beautiful despite daily wear and tear. Whether you go with Benjamin Moore Regal Select for its durability or Behr Marquee for its one-coat convenience, investing in high-quality, washable, and stain-resistant paint will make a big difference.
